long_desc.thetext:
In your example, if you hold down the CTRL key in the target, you'll be able to perform the drop.

The documentation states that:
 * If the application does not set the <code>event.detail</code> to something other than <code>DND.DROP_DEFAULT</code> the operation will be set to the platform defined standard default.

On Windows, the default operation is DND.DROP_MOVE if the application does not specify its own operation. If the target only supports the DND.DROP_COPY and the default operation is DND.DROP_MOVE, you will not be able to perform the drop.

To fix the problem, you should set the event.detail to DND.DROP_COPY if you only want to support copy. Eg,

	public void dragEnter(DropTargetEvent e) {
		e.detail = DND.DROP_COPY;
	}

