The problem seems to be with the applyChangesNow() call.

UI opens a module through Model'a API in SessionHandle.openLibrary/openDesign. During this operation, session will keep the instance of the opened module. So if the instance is no longer in use, UI should call ModuleHandle.close() to drop it from session. Otherwise, the unused instance can not be cleaned and reused by java's garbage collector.

e.g.
LibraryExplorerProvider.java Line 89,

used to be:
return super.getChildren( SessionHandleAdapter.getInstance( ).getSessionHandle( ).openLibrary( file.getAbsolutePath( ) ) );

should be:
LibraryHandle library = SessionHandleAdapter.getInstance( ).getSessionHandle( ).openLibrary(file.getAbsolutePath( ) );
Object[] rtns = super.getChildren( library );
library.close( );
return rtns;

Will there be memory leak if this line

Object[] rtns = super.getChildren( library );

throws exception?

